        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12685.xml">letter to R. P. Hardy, 11 August [1880]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"> Hardy was reviewing the accounts of the Down Friendly Club to determine whether sickness benefits could be increased (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12677.xml">letter to J. M. F. Ludlow, 4 August 1880</ref>, and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12680.xml">letter to R. P. Hardy, 6 August [1880]</ref>). The enclosures have not been found; the accounts for the club prior to 1875 had been lost (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12685.xml">letter to R. P. Hardy, 11 August [1880]</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">The chief registrar of friendly societies was <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3034.xml">John Malcolm Forbes Ludlow</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">The note has not been found; the Rules of the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1370.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Down Friendly Society</ref> are in the National Archives, FS1/232.</note>
            
            
